HEADWORD: Nautiloid
<hw>Nau"ti*loid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Nautilus</ets> + <ets>-oid</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>nautilo⟦ium⟧de</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Like or
pertaining to the nautilus; shaped like a nautilus shell.</def> --
<def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>A mollusk, or shell, of the genus
<gen>Nautilus</gen> or family <fam>Nautilidae</fam>.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

